<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>With the energy department due to release new fuel prices next week, the AA yesterday said the price of crude oil had hiked while the rand weakened against the dollar.It revealed the price of petrol could jump by 72c a litre while diesel could go up by 54c a litre. The price of illuminating paraffin could rise by 76c. Earlier this month, the AA said: “Concerns over government’s fiscal discipline are likely to continue weighing heavily on the rand.” SunLanders on social media weren’t happy to learn petrol prices were likely to go up yet again. The following were among the comments on Facebook: Reso Mosepele: “This will definitely undermine consumers’ ability to spend and save. The poor will be hardest hit as day-to-day supplies become more expensive.”Mthizman Thelamanzi: “Can anyone help me with the government’s contact number? I need to swear at our leaders like hell. We are sick and tired of petrol price hikes!” Chris Joubert: “Why are we feeding corruption in the South African government by allowing them to increase the petrol price again?”